41','2014-08-16 02:01:41','<script src=\"http://localhost/forum/js/embed.js\"></script>','Community','','publish','closed','open','','community','','','2014-08-16 21:22:48','2014-08-16 21:22:48','',0,'http://localhost/discussions-2/',0,'page','',0),(23,1,'2014-08-16 02:51:01','2014-08-16 02:51:01','Here at Healing Over Time, we think online communities are great. No, really, we do. When gamers pool their collective talents and passions together into the melting pot of social interaction wonderful things can happen, both online and offline. From safe and welcoming spaces for people of any gender, orientation, or preference to overwhelmingly strong support for charities all across the globe, online communities can be a positive force in the world, and that’s why we exist.\r\n\r\nWe believe that investing in the state of online communities is a worthwhile task, and by providing useful resources and support to the leaders and members of online groups, we hope to encourage a healthier and more welcoming online environment for everyone to enjoy.\r\n\r\nBut who are we? Well, Healing Over Time is made up of an eclectic bunch of individuals, but we all hail from a variety of MMO games. Whether its a dedicated regime of gear grinding spanning several years, or simply idling around our favorite virtual spaces whilst having a good chat, we know what it’s like to connect with a friendly group of like-minded players and we won’t trade that feeling for the world.\r\n\r\nRight now we’re busy tinkering away in the background, preparing everything we need to provide the best support we can for those who need it, so be sure to watch this space.\r\n\r\nIf you want to get in touch with us, the best way for now is <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/HealingOverTime\">through Twitter</a>.','About Healing Over Time','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2014-11-11 18:40:41','2014-11-11 18:40:41','',0,'http://localhost/?page_id=23',0,'page','',0),(24,1,'2014-08-16 02:51:01','2014-08-16 02:51:01','As gamers, we know the enjoyment and benefits that our hobbies and careers can bring. Many of us will have fond memories of playing with or against our siblings, parents and friends. For some, gaming will have helped us through a tough time in our lives. Unfortunately this isn\'t an experience that can be shared with everyone, due to illness, poverty and war.\r\n\r\nHealing Over Time brings gamers from all walks of life and locations around the world to reach out to those who need a helping hand. Organisations of gamers play the games they love, have bonded over, and are excited about for 24 hours, hoping that their fun and community spirit will reach out to those who need it most.\r\n\r\nOf course, one of the best ways of doing this is by raising money for charities with connections to those in need. Every charity we raise money for works internationally and aims to improve the health and life of others. This time around we\'ll be raising money for Child\'s Play.\r\n\r\nHealing Over Time started life in December 2012 as MYSTathon. 8 members of the guild Mystic Spiral [MYST] played DOTA2 and Guild Wars 2 for 24 hours, supported by more than 10 other members. The event raised over $525 for Child\'s Play. It was so much fun they decided to do it again and get other guilds involved, leading to the creation of Healing Over Time.\r\n\r\nThis March, our staff will be joined by Mystic Spiral, Enigma, Relics of Orr, Afterlife, Dragon Season, Subterfuge Gaming, BOON Control, and Viking Nation during Healing Over Time. With prizes and good times ahead we hope you\'ll help us smash our target of $5000.\r\n\r\nTogether, we\'ll show the world the benefits of gaming, one hour at a time.','About','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-08-16 02:51:01','2014-08-16 02:51:01','',23,'http://localhost/2014/08/23-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2014-08-16 02:51:34','2014-08-16 02:51:34','','About','','publish','open','open','','25','','','2014-08-26 18:41:20','2014-08-26 18:41:20','',0,'http://localhost/?p=25',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(26,1,'2014-11-11 18:39:29','2014-11-11 18:39:29','Here at Healing Over Time, we think online communities are great. No, really, we do. When gamers pool their collective talents and passions together into the melting pot of social interaction wonderful things can happen, both online and offline. From safe and welcoming spaces for people of any gender, orientation, or preference to overwhelmingly strong support for charities all across the globe, online communities can be a positive force in the world, and that’s why we exist.\n\nWe believe that investing in the state of online communities is a worthwhile task, and by providing useful resources and support to the leaders and members of online groups, we hope to encourage a healthier and more welcoming online environment for everyone to enjoy.\n\nBut who are we? Well, Healing Over Time is made up of an eclectic bunch of individuals, but we all hail from a variety of MMO games. Whether its a dedicated regime of gear grinding spanning several years, or simply idling around our favorite virtual spaces whilst having a good chat, we know what it’s like to connect with a friendly group of like-minded players and we won’t trade that feeling for the world.\n\nRight now we’re busy tinkering away in the background, preparing everything we need to provide the best support we can for those who need it, so be sure to watch this space.\n\nIf you want to get in touch with us, the best way for now is through Twi','About Healing Over Time','','inherit','open','open','','23-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-11 18:39:29','2014-11-11 18:39:29','',23,'http://localhost/2014/08/23-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2014-08-16 03:19:46','2014-08-16 03:19:46','Healing Over Time brings gamers from all walks of life and locations around the world to reach out to those who need a helping hand, no matter where they are.\r\n\r\nWe do this by making it easier for gamers to raise money for their chosen charities and by putting gamers in touch with people, organisations and charities that can benefit them.\r\n<h2>Our Aims</h2>\r\n<h3>Raise the profile of gaming</h3>\r\nThere are people doing good in gaming every day. Be it a chance encounter that helps a new player on their journey, or a large community running a sucessful fundraising event for a good cause, everyone contributes to a positive environment in virtual worlds.\r\n\r\nWe aim to highlight and encourage this positive behaviour, making it easier for gamers to be great citizens.\r\n<h3>Education and support</h3>\r\nJust like any other community, gamers and their families face a wide range of challenges from a variety of sources.\r\n\r\nWe aim to work with other charities and organisations to provide gamers with relevant information and support on a variety of issues, including but not limited to, physical and mental health, conflict resolution, online privacy, harassment, exclusion and accessibility.\r\n<h2>Core beliefs</h2>\r\nTransparency\r\n\r\nEquality\r\n\r\nPassion\r\n<h2>Fundraising</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Organisation Structure</h2>\r\nHealing Over Time is applying to become a non-profit organisation within the United Kingdom. This allows us to minimise our expenditure whilst still being as productive as we possibly can be.\r\n\r\nEveryone supporting the organisation is a volunteer, and all staff members are passionate gamers.','About','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-08-16 03:19:46','2014-08-16 03:19:46','',23,'http://localhost/2014/08/23-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(28,1,'2014-08-16 09:05:00','2014-08-16 09:05:00','','Discussions','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-v1','','','2014-08-16 09:05:00','2014-08-16 09:05:00','',22,'http://localhost/2014/08/22-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2014-08-16 09:06:31','2014-08-16 09:06:31','<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://localhost/forum/js/embed.js\"></script>